The set of β
m and β
h parameters given by Hall-Mendelin et al. [ 37] provides the lowest R
hv values, while the set of β
m and β
h parameters given by Duchemin et al. [ 27] provides the highest values. For consistency, we present the results only based on the set of parameters published by Hugo, Stassen et al. (2019), providing an intermediate set of β
m and β
h parameters. Fig 1 presents locations where R
hv >0 throughout the entire year (i.e. Brisbane, Cairns, Darwin, Rockhampton, Thursday Island, Townsville) ( Fig 1). The locations were the same when either species of mosquito were considered. For both species, R
hv was highest in Cairns, followed by Darwin, Thursday Island, Rockhampton, Townsville and finally Brisbane.
